Job URL: http://ABOUT US Card Kingdom is an online retailer that specializes in selling and buying Magic: The Gathering singles. Noted for their love of the community and game, Card Kingdom serves gamers all over the world. In addition to its eCommerce business, Card Kingdom owns and operates the award-winning game store and restaurant, Mox Boarding House, with locations in Seattle and Bellevue, and coming soon to Portland.  Card Kingdom’s headquarters are located on Queen Anne, and just a short drive to Mox Seattle.  JOB DESCRIPTION Card Kingdom is looking for the first-ever UX/UI designer to join our eCommerce team. This role is responsible for creating intuitive and thoughtful UI wireframes / prototypes / flows from business requirements, while also being the voice of usability across both external and internal systems. They will also be responsible for creating highly-optimized production art assets, that are consistent with Card Kingdom’s brand and appealing to our audience.  ROLE OBJECTIVES · Own the end-to-end design process and deliverables (including user personas, workflows, interactive wire-frames, mock-ups, and production art assets). · Work closely with our Agile sprint teams on the ever-changing requirements of our retail and online business. · Lead the planning and execution of consumer research at every stage of the product/feature lifecycle; from concept, prototype validations, all the way to usability tests on the final creation. · Balance your time and efforts across all the teams that need it - you ARE the design team! · Be future-looking with your designs but also understand the realities of shipping code. · Communicate complex, interactive design concepts clearly across different audiences and varying levels of the organization. · Understand how to utilize data to inform design decisions. · Empathize with the struggles of our users and be a customer advocate whether that is a customer ordering on their phone or an employee packing that same order.  QUALIFICATIONS · Bachelor’s Degree or 3+ years of related experience preferable. · Excellent communication, presentation, interpersonal and analytical skills. · Previous experience working with retail and/or online sales + fulfillment pipelines a plus. · Familiarity with A/B, multivariate, and other quantitative testing techniques.  · An online portfolio or samples of work demonstrating experience creating great end-to-end, user- centered design solutions and patterns, across desktop and mobile devices.  · Proficiency designing and prototyping with a variety of tools such as Photoshop, Illustrator, InDesign, Sketch Cloud, After Effects or similar. · Self-motivated, self-directed, with a positive outlook and “can-do” attitude. Our Benefits: Generous PTO policy, Excellent Health Benefit plans, 401k matching, Paid Holidays, Employee Discounts. Equal Opportunity Employment: We are committed to cultivating a workplace in which diverse perspectives and experiences are welcomed and respected. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, color, religion, creed, ancestry, national origin, sex, age, disability (physical or mental), marital or veteran status, genetic information, sexual orientation, gender identity, political ideology, or membership in any other legally protected class.

Job URL: http://The CINC Product Team is looking for a UX designer interested in working across mobile experiences to define and deliver user-centered design solutions. meet deadlines  • You keep up with the latest design trends, patterns, and technologies, and can provide feedback and new ideas  • You are familiar with mobile UX design and the unique design
